    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="656"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d656">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File 838.77/109.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Blanchard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 23, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You are instructed to inform [President] Theodore that the Government of the
                    United States hopes that foreclosure proceedings against the American railroad
                    will be suspended until such time as all questions pending between the railroad
                    and the Haitian Government can be fully considered here. The disturbed
                    conditions there should be taken into consideration.</p>
                <p>Report by telegraph result of your representations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
